This demo displays the voice recognition service capability. You can tap the voice detection button to enable the microphone to continuously recognize surrounding sounds. \n\nThe function may be used to assist in receiving a surrounding sound signal, so as to remind a user to make a timely response when an emergency occurs. \n\nIf a specified type of sound is displayed, the recognition result is displayed. Tap Stop to stop voice recognition. \n\nCurrently, the voice recognition service supports 13 voice types, include infant or child cry, shout, cat bark, dog bark, water, knock, door bell, car horn, fire alarm, alarm, laughter, sneeze, and snoring.

Before using the image super-resolution service, you need to convert the image into a bitmap in ARGB format, and the output bitmap format is also ARGB. \nIn the 3x super resolution scenario, the maximum size of the input image is 800 x 800 pixels, and the minimum size is not less than 64 x 64 pixels. \nIn the 1x super resolution scenario, the maximum size of an input image is 1024px x 768px or 768px x 1024px, the minimum size is 64px x 64px. \nThe effect is not obvious when the input picture is of good quality and definition. Before using the text image super-resolution service, you need to convert the image into a bitmap in ARGB format, and the output bitmap format is also ARGB. \nOnly 3x super resolution is supported. The maximum size of an input image is 800px x 800px, and the minimum size is 64px x 64px. \nThe effect is not obvious when the input picture is of good quality and definition. The image segmentation service divides the elements in an image (such as the human body, plant, and sky) into segments along with their location.\nSupports segmentation of static images and dynamic camera streams. Supports fine segmentation.\n\nCurrently supported items include: human body, sky, plant, food, cat, dog, flower, water, sand, building, mountain and others.\nThe return value of multi-class partitioning is the coordinate array of each element.
